text: The Piney Point Phosphate Mine discharged wastewater into Tampa Bay during the early spring of 2021 which led to the worst red tide event & fish kill on record in the Tampa Bay estuary.  Tides and currents helped carry nutrients & concentrated karenia brevis out of the Bay.
